<setup>
  <boolean name="Acorrect">$A.creditAchieved=1</boolean>
  <boolean name="Bcorrect">$B.creditAchieved=1</boolean>
  <boolean name="Ccorrect">$C.creditAchieved=1</boolean>
  <boolean name="Dcorrect">$D.creditAchieved=1</boolean>  
  <boolean name="Ecorrect">$E.creditAchieved=1</boolean>
  <boolean name="Fcorrect">$F.creditAchieved=1</boolean> 
</setup>  
<p>
  For each of the following indefinite integrals, identify if the integral could be evaluated using substitution, integration by parts, or neither.  For each integral, once you identify the correct approach, you'll be prompted to enter the appropriate substitution (if there is one).  There is no need to actually evaluate any of the integrals.
</p>

<p>
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>\int x \sin(x^2) \, dx</m>
        <answer name="A"><choiceInput>
          <choice credit="1">substitution</choice>
          <choice>integration by parts</choice>
          <choice>neither</choice>
        </choiceInput></answer>  
      </p>
      <p hide="not $Acorrect">
          The substitution to use is <m>u = </m><mathInput name="uA"/>, <m>du = </m><mathInput name="duA"/> <m>dx</m> <answer><award><when>$uA = x^2 and $duA = 2x</when></award></answer>
      </p>
    </li>    
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>\int x^2 \sin(x) \, dx </m>
        <answer name="B"><choiceInput>
          <choice>substitution</choice>
          <choice credit="1">integration by parts</choice>
          <choice>neither</choice>
        </choiceInput></answer>  
      </p>
      <p hide="not $Bcorrect">
          The substitution to use is <m>u = </m><mathInput name="uB"/>, <m>du = </m><mathInput name="duB"/> <m>dx</m>, <m>dv = </m><mathInput name="dvB"/><m>dx</m>, <m>v = </m><mathInput name="vB"/> <answer><award><when>$uB = x^2 and $duB = 2x and $dvB = sin(x) and $vB = -cos(x) </when></award></answer>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>\int \sin(x^2) \, dx </m>
        <answer name="C"><choiceInput>
          <choice>substitution</choice>
          <choice>integration by parts</choice>
          <choice credit="1">neither</choice>
        </choiceInput></answer>  
      </p>
    </li>    
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>\int x \ln(x) \, dx </m>
        <answer name="D"><choiceInput>
          <choice>substitution</choice>
          <choice credit="1">integration by parts</choice>
          <choice>neither</choice>
        </choiceInput></answer>  
      </p>
      <p hide="not $Dcorrect">
          The substitution to use is <m>u = </m><mathInput name="uD"/>, <m>du = </m><mathInput name="duD"/> <m>dx</m>, <m>dv = </m><mathInput name="dvD"/><m>dx</m>, <m>v = </m><mathInput name="vD"/> <answer><award><when>$uD = ln(x) and $duD = 1/x and $dvD = x and $vD = 1/2*x^2 </when></award></answer>
      </p>
    </li> 
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>\displaystyle \int \frac{\ln(x)}{x} \, dx </m>
        <answer name="E"><choiceInput>
          <choice credit="1">substitution</choice>
          <choice>integration by parts</choice>
          <choice>neither</choice>
        </choiceInput></answer>  
      </p>
      <p hide="not $Ecorrect">
          The substitution to use is <m>u = </m><mathInput name="uE"/>, <m>du = </m><mathInput name="duE"/> <m>dx</m> <answer><award><when>$uE = ln(x) and $duE = 1/x</when></award></answer>
      </p>      
    </li>    
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>\int \ln(x) \, dx </m>
        <answer name="F"><choiceInput>
          <choice>substitution</choice>
          <choice credit="1">integration by parts</choice>
          <choice>neither</choice>
        </choiceInput></answer>  
      </p>
      <p hide="not $Fcorrect">
          The substitution to use is <m>u = </m><mathInput name="uF"/>, <m>du = </m><mathInput name="duF"/> <m>dx</m>, <m>dv = </m><mathInput name="dvF"/><m>dx</m>, <m>v = </m><mathInput name="vF"/> <answer><award><when>$uF = ln(x) and $duF = 1/x and $dvF = 1 and $vF = x </when></award></answer>
      </p>
    </li>      
  </ol>
</p>